Usage
-----

.. code:: console

   $ ttyszfury --help
   usage: ttyszfury [-h] [-t TTY] [--min-width N] [--max-width N] [--min-height N] [--max-height N] [--interval N] [COMMAND]

   positional arguments:
     COMMAND            command to execute

   options:
     -h, --help         show this help message and exit
     -t TTY, --tty TTY  terminal device to resize (default: stdin)
     --min-width N      minimum terminal width (default: 1)
     --max-width N      maximum terminal width (default: original width)
     --min-height N     minimum terminal height (default: 1)
     --max-height N     maximum terminal height (default: original height)
     --interval N       delay between resizes, in seconds (default: no delay)

Example
-------

.. code:: console

   $ ulimit -c unlimited

   $ ttyszfury -- info coreutils
   ttyszfury: target program terminated by SIGSEGV (core dumped)

